                       up money for education, health, defence, housing and overseas aid. Unions oppose the plans but Mr
                                                                                                                        
                       Brown said 2bn savings had already been made and more jobs had been cut than had been expected at
                                                                                                                        
                       this stage. A further 200 jobs at the Department of the Environment, Food and Rural Affairs have 
                                                                                                                        
